quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  17,78,"Be thou steadfast in prayer from the declining of the sun until the dusk of the night, and the reading of the dawn; verily, the reading of the dawn is ever testified to"
  17,79,"And for the night, watch thou therein as an extra service. It may be that thy Lord will raise thee to a laudable station"
  17,80,"And say, 'O my Lord! make me enter with a just entry; and make me come forth with a just coming forth; and grant me from, Thee authority to aid"
  17,81,"And say, 'Truth has come, and falsehood has vanished! verily, falsehood is transient"
  17,82,"And we will send down of the Qur'an that which is a healing and a mercy to the believers, but it will only increase the wrong-doers in loss"
  17,83,"And when we favour man he turns away and retires aside, but when evil touches him he is ever in despair"
  17,84,"Say, 'Every one acts after his own manner, but your Lord knows, best who is most guided in the way"